==English==
=== Noun ===
'''[[interrogative]] [[pronoun]]'''

#{{grammar}} A pronoun used in a question. In English, the five interrogative pronouns are ''[[what]]'', ''[[which]]'', ''[[who]]'', ''[[whom]]'', and ''[[whose]]'' (also used as [[relative pronoun]]s). These require no antecedent. The suffixes -ever and -soever may be added to ''what'', ''which'', ''who'', and ''whom''.
#:''What'' did you say?
#:''Who'' said that?
#:To ''whom'' was that said?
#:''Which'' student said that?
#:''Whose'' question was that?

